<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
MEXICO. Hidalgo, Cumbre de Jacala, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. Matuda</emphasis>
37288 (holotype MEXU00050769).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Trailing or climbing plant, stems finely pilose, glabrescent. Leaves petiolate, 4-9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-7 cm, ovate-deltoid, obtuse, base cordate and then cuneate onto the petiole with distinct rounded auricles, margin irregularly dentate, both surfaces green, abaxially paler, strongly reticulate, veins pubescent; petioles 2-5 cm. Inflorescence of 1-3 flowered, axillary cymes; peduncles 10-15 cm; bracteoles 1-4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-3.5 cm, ovate, petiolate, dentate, resembling small leaves; pedicels 14-22 mm, tickened upwards, pubescent; sepals subequal, 15-17 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6 mm, narrowly oblong-elliptic, acuminate, margin scarious, outer sepals pubescent, glabrescent; corolla 5.5-6.5 cm long, funnel-shaped, pinkish-purple with paler tube, glabrous, limb c. 3 cm diam. Capsules and seed unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Endemic to Hidalgo in Mexico and only known from the type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">MEXICO. Hidalgo</emphasis>
: type collection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The leaf shape suggests this species is intermediate between 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea stans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and another species, perhaps 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orizabensis">I. orizabensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The foliose bracteoles and dentate leaves are distinctive characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
